<br>
"The Matrix: Reloaded" - in theaters May 15<br>
   - ends in large action sequence with car chase on crowded freeway constructed in Alameda just for the movie (formerly the naval base in Star Trek IV).  Oh, by the way; it costs $300,000 to make a quarter mile of freeway.<br>
   - introduces Keymaker (Randall Duk Kim), Niobe (Jada Pinkett Smith), the Twins (Neil and Adrian Rayment), Persephone(Monica Belucci), Seraph (Lung Yun Chou),and Zion (it's a place, remember).  Morpheus, Trinity, and Neo still around<br>
   - Neo has accepted that he is the One.  The machines have found Zion, the last human city, and plan on invading it with tons of sentinels.  Neo, M, and T have to get the Keymaker who can open doors to the machine world and is being guarded by the Twins (albino, dreadlocked black-belts that can switch places in the Matrix without jumping to other peoples' bodies).  Agent Smith has learned to self-replicate (no Turtle Wax please), making some cool fights possible.<br>
   - introduces technique called "virtual cinematography" that begins by using five digital cameras to capture the actors actions and are detailed enough to pick up stuff like individual hairs moving.  A computer churns the data and constructs an extremely accurate 3-D model of the actor and then puts it in the scene and can be programmed to do stuff.  So when Agent Smith(s) go to beatdown Neo, try to find the real Elrond.<br>
<br>
"The Matrix: Revolutions" - in theaters November 2003<br>
   - without revealing anymore info from Reloaded, this one is basically a war between the machines and humans.  Takes place outside of the matrix, in the ruins of the real world.<br>
<br>
"The Animatrix" - available soon<br>
   - 9 animated movies, 4 of which are downloadable soon (sometime in February)<br>
   - Recommended ones: "The Final Flight of the Osiris", "Second Renaissance" (two parts)<br>
<br>
Enter the Matrix - video game featuring Niobe and Ghost, no idea what format or when its coming out (sometime in 2003).  Shot an additional hour of real footage to integrate into the game, like in the LOTR game. <p>He has the constitution of a vending machine! -- Cobra Commander</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bheavyhand65062.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantomnomad@heavyhand65062>phantom nomad</A> at: 1/16/03 11:51:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=404040><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bheavyhand65062.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantomnomad@heavyhand65062>phantom nomad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ZOINKS!</span><br>  Posts: 105<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/9/03 11:31:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.heavyhand.org/shaggy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;The Year of the Matrix&quot;</span><hr size=1> Some more updates (from InQuest #96)<br>
<br>
The website for the Animatrix DVD is up and some of the episodes are up for download. <br>
<a href="http://www.theanimatrix.com" target="_new">www.theanimatrix.com</a><br>
The actual DVD will be released on June 3rd.<br>
>"The Second Renaissance: Part 1" - prequel history of the war between mankind and the machines, written by the Wachowski brothers (posted Feb, I wouldn't recommend watching this just yet since part 2 comes out in May)<br>
>"Program" - In the simulated world of a samurai training program a soldier of Zion must choose between love and her comrades in the real world (posted March 1)<br>
>"Detective Story" - A hard-boiled private detective tracks cyber-criminal Trinity through the wonderland of the matrix (April)<br>
>"The Second Renaissance: Part 2" - conclusion of story behing humanity's downfall and their enslavement by the machines<br>
<br>
The movie "Dreamcatcher" to be released on March 21 will be preceded by the Animatrix episode "The Final Flight of Osiris".  Osiris occurs between the original Matrix and Reloaded (opens in May).  "The Matrix: Reloaded" will be followed by the trailer for "The Matrix: Revisited." <p>&quot;... whereever you rub it, it always feels better, ...&quot; - Brak</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bheavyhand65062.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantomnomad@heavyhand65062>phantom nomad</A> at: 3/9/03 11:45:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#404040><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bheavyhand65062.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calistra>calistra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Techno Monkey</span><br>  Posts: 1026<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/10/03 12:04:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gallopsstuff.com/images/webpage/callistra.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &quot;The Year of the Matrix&quot;</span><hr size=1> good to know our IMDB reporter is on top of things, thanks shaggy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=340.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=340.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=2><img src=http://heavyhand.org/buttonreply2.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fheavyhand65062frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=340.topic